{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586991","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586991"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:41:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:41:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15119"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15119","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15119"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.46,0.38,0,0.17,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7807"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116386"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7807","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7807"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15119"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98384"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"10000"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19037"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19040"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20425"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116386","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116386"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAchalasia is an uncommon, but important oesophageal disorder. The patient typically presents with a long history of many months or several years of difficulty in swallowing. The condition is characterised by impaired relaxation of the lower oesophageal sphincter and loss of peristalsis in the distal oesophagus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a chronic manifestation of achalasia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dilatation of the oesophagus","Narrowing of the oesophagus","Increased peristalsis","Decreased sphincter tone","Mucosal atrophy"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn long-standing achalasia, the persistent functional obstruction at the lower oesophageal sphincter leads to several changes. \u003Cstrong\u003EDilatation of oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to chronic food retention and fluid accumulation above the functionally obstructed lower oesophageal sphincter. The dilatation is often associated with tortuosity of the oesophagus (Image). Other chronic manifestations include food retention, chronic inflammation, and increased risk of squamous cell carcinoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENarrowing of oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur as the opposite happens with progressive dilatation. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased peristalsis\u003C/strong\u003E does not develop since achalasia is characterised by decreased or absent peristalsis. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased sphincter tone\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur as there is failure of sphincter relaxation rather than reduced tone. \u003Cstrong\u003EMucosal atrophy\u003C/strong\u003E is not a typical finding as chronic inflammation and hyperplasia may occur instead.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Chronic achalasia leads to oesophageal dilatation, not reduction in size","Chronic achalasia can cause oesophageal dilatation, food retention, inflammation, and increased cancer risk","Complications of chronic achalasia include aspiration pneumonia and squamous cell carcinoma"],"references":["Pandolfino JE, Gawron AJ. Achalasia: a systematic review. JAMA. 2015 May 12;313(18):1841-52. doi: 10.1001/jama.2015.2996. PMID: 25965233.","Panebianco M, Marchese-Ragona R, Masiero S, Restivo DA. Dysphagia in neurological diseases: a literature review. Neurol Sci. 2020 Nov;41(11):3067-3073. doi: 10.1007/s10072-020-04495-2. Epub 2020 Jun 7. PMID: 32506360; PMCID: PMC7567719","Wilkinson JM, Codipilly DC, Wilfahrt RP. Dysphagia: Evaluation and Collaborative Management. Am Fam Physician. 2021 Jan 15;103(2):97-106. PMID: 33448766","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98384"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15119"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21185"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21185","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21185"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/Oc0kcMErtbK9nr9EY4i7kr451Svrlp.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/Oc0kcMErtbK9nr9EY4i7kr451Svrlp.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":433,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98384"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-28T19:56:28+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T19:56:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7807"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116386"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student"